usage: reframe [-h] [--prefix DIR] [-o DIR] [-s DIR] [--logdir DIR] [--keep-stage-files] [--save-log-files] [-c DIR|FILE] [-R]
               [--ignore-check-conflicts] [-t TAGS] [-n NAME] [-x NAME] [-p PRGENV] [--gpu-only] [--cpu-only] [-l] [-r] [-A ACCOUNT] [-P PART]
               [--reservation RES] [--nodelist NODELIST] [--exclude-nodes NODELIST] [--job-option OPT] [--force-local] [--skip-sanity-check]
               [--skip-performance-check] [--strict] [--skip-system-check] [--skip-prgenv-check] [--exec-policy POLICY] [--mode MODE]
               [--max-retries NUM] [-m MOD] [-M MAPPING] [--module-mappings FILE] [--nocolor] [--timestamp [TIMEFMT]] [--system SYSTEM]
               [-C FILE] [-V]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit

Options controlling regression directories:
  --prefix DIR          Set regression prefix directory to DIR
  -o DIR, --output DIR  Set regression output directory to DIR
  -s DIR, --stage DIR   Set regression stage directory to DIR
  --logdir DIR          Set regression log directory to DIR
  --keep-stage-files    Keep stage directory even if check is successful
  --save-log-files      Copy the log file from the work dir to the output dir at the end of the program

Options for locating checks:
  -c DIR|FILE, --checkpath DIR|FILE
                        Search for checks in DIR or FILE
  -R, --recursive       Load checks recursively
  --ignore-check-conflicts
                        Skip checks with conflicting names

Options for selecting checks:
  -t TAGS, --tag TAGS   Select checks matching TAG
  -n NAME, --name NAME  Select checks with NAME
  -x NAME, --exclude NAME
                        Exclude checks with NAME
  -p PRGENV, --prgenv PRGENV
                        Select tests for PRGENV programming environment only
  --gpu-only            Select only GPU tests
  --cpu-only            Select only CPU tests

Options controlling actions:
  -l, --list            list matched regression checks
  -r, --run             Run regression with the selected checks

Options controlling execution of checks:
  -A ACCOUNT, --account ACCOUNT
                        Use ACCOUNT for submitting jobs
  -P PART, --partition PART
                        Use PART for submitting jobs
  --reservation RES     Use RES for submitting jobs
  --nodelist NODELIST   Run checks on the selected list of nodes
  --exclude-nodes NODELIST
                        Exclude the list of nodes from running checks
  --job-option OPT      Pass OPT to job scheduler
  --force-local         Force local execution of checks
  --skip-sanity-check   Skip sanity checking
  --skip-performance-check
                        Skip performance checking
  --strict              Force strict performance checking
  --skip-system-check   Skip system check
  --skip-prgenv-check   Skip prog. environment check
  --exec-policy POLICY  Specify the execution policy for running the regression tests. Available policies: "serial" (default), "async"
  --mode MODE           Execution mode to use
  --max-retries NUM     Specify the maximum number of times a failed regression test may be retried (default: 0)

Miscellaneous options:
  -m MOD, --module MOD  Load module MOD before running the regression
  -M MAPPING, --map-module MAPPING
                        Apply a single module mapping
  --module-mappings FILE
                        Apply module mappings defined in FILE
  --nocolor             Disable coloring of output
  --timestamp [TIMEFMT]
                        Append a timestamp component to the regression directories(default format "%FT%T")
  --system SYSTEM       Load SYSTEM configuration explicitly
  -C FILE, --config-file FILE
                        Specify a custom config-file for the machine. (default:
                        /apps/common/UES/jenkins/SLES12/easybuild/software/reframe/2.12/reframe/settings.py
  -V, --version         show program's version number and exit
